The paper deals with ontology-mediated queries (OMQs) and their implementation using first-order queries and SQL databases. This topic is closely related to databases (cs.DB) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI), as OMQs are used in knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper specifically focuses on the description logic \(\mathcal{EL}\) (cs.LO) and conjunctive queries (cs.CR), and presents an algorithm for computing first-order rewritings of OMQs based on atomic queries. Finally, the paper includes experiments with real-world ontologies, which suggests a practical application of the proposed approach (cs.DL).
